iate nor predictive for the small scales probed by\nabsorption line observations of the CGM. Local conditions generally cannot be\nderived by assuming a global equilibrium, but an emergent global equilibrium\nbalancing radially inward and outward forces is obtained when averaging over\nthe non-equilibrium local conditions on large scales in space and time.\nApproximate hydrostatic equilibrium holds only at large distances from galaxies\neven when averaging out small-scale variations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 20 Jun 2022 18:00:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 7 Mar 2023 16:39:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-10"}
